    <h2>ColorDiff</h2>
    <h3>Colour-highlighted 'diff' output</h3>
    <h4>Updated - version 1.0.9 released on Tuesday 21 April 2009</h4>

    <p>The Perl script colordiff is a wrapper for 'diff' and produces the same
    output but with pretty 'syntax' highlighting. Colour schemes can be
    customized.</p>

    <p>To see how colordiff works, you can
    
    <ul>
    <li>read the <a href="colordiff.html">man page</a> (auto-generated from XML
    source), and 
    <li>view some <a href="screenshots.html">screenshots</a>
    <li>read the <a href="changes.html">changelog</a>
    </ul>

    <p>Download colordiff:
    
    <ul>
    <li> Latest version: <a
    href="colordiff-1.0.9.tar.gz">colordiff-1.0.9.tar.gz</a>
    <li> PGP signature for latest version:
    <a href="colordiff-1.0.9.tar.gz.sig">colordiff-1.0.9.tar.gz.sig</a>
    </ul>

    <p>Availability of colordiff with your Linux/BSD distribution:

    <ul>
    <li><p><a href="http://www.debian.org/">Debian</a> and <a
href="http://www.ubuntu.com/">Ubuntu</a> users can probably just use
    "apt-get install colordiff" to download and install;</p>
    <li>colordiff has been packaged for <a href="http://www.gentoo.org">Gentoo
    Linux</a>;
    <li>colordiff has been packaged for <a href="http://fedora.redhat.com/">Fedora</a>;
    <li>colordiff has been ported to <a
    href="http://developer.apple.com/darwin/">MacOS X/Darwin</a>;
    <li>colordiff is available with <a href="http://www.lunar-linux.org">Lunar
    Linux</a>;
    <li>colordiff has been ported to <a
    href="http://www.freebsd.org/">FreeBSD</a>;
    </ul>

    <p>PGP key is available from <a href="http://www.sungate.co.uk/">my home
    page</a>.</p>

    <p>To receive notification of new versions and other announcements, please
    join the <a
    href="http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/colordiff-announce">colordiff-announce</a>
    mailing list.  There is also a user/developer mailing list to discuss
    features of the program and to report bugs, post patches etc. - join the <a
    href="http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/colordiff-misc">colordiff-misc</a>
    mailing list.</p>

